OM_02: Lower M

The natural mortality rate (M) is reduced from the Base Case value of 0.107 to the lower value considered in the assessment sensitivity tests.

Red Snapper

M for mature adults is reduced from 0.107 (Base Case) to 0.07.

Gag

M for mature adults is reduced from 0.172 (Base Case) to 0.10.
